In recent days, the U.S. stock market is fluctuating because of investor panic, the fastest rise in inflation in decades, and the Federal Reserve forced to launch the biggest monetary tightening measures since the 1980s. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng takes you back to the recent U.S. stock market performance and analyzes whether the Fed can successfully implement the plan of raising interest rates and shrinking the balance sheet without dragging the economy into recession.